2001-04-29  mark van schilfgaarde  <markv@waldo.ran.sandia.gov>

        * can read/write restart file in ascii mode.
          --rs=#1,#2 changed switches to :
            #1 = 0 => overlap atomic densities  (identical to old version)
                 1 => read from binary rst file (identical to old version)
                 2 => read from ascii rsta file
                 add 10 to invoke smshft 
            #2 = 0 => do not write to rst file  (identical to old version)  
                 1 => save in binary rst file   (identical to old version)  
                 2 => sae in  ascii rsta file
        
2001-04-25  mark van schilfgaarde  <markv@waldo.ran.sandia.gov>

        * New definition for constant potential: defined to be average of
          electrostatic potentials at MT boundaries.  This puts lmf in
          accordance with old FP and ASA conventions with the Fermi level
          typically falling nar zero.  --oldvc recovers the original convention.

        * Simplified how a plane is specified in writing charge densities

        * Some small bug fixes

